**Title:** Goodbye, Moon Face: How Carnivore Reveals Your True Jawline
**Summary:** Tired of the morning puff? Discover how ditching carbs flushes water weight and inflammation to reveal your hidden cheekbones.

***

# Goodbye, Puffy Face: The De-bloating and De-puffing Effect

Ever wake up, look in the mirror, and feel like you’ve transformed into a marshmallow overnight? We’ve all been there. That heavy, swollen feeling—often affectionately (or not so affectionately) called "Moon Face"—is a common struggle.

But here is the good news: One of the very first things people notice when they switch to the Carnivore Diet isn’t just the scale moving; it’s their face changing shape.

If you are ready to trade the puffiness for a chiseled jawline, here is why steak might just be your new favorite beauty hack.

## The Carb-Sponge Connection

To understand the puff, we have to talk about carbohydrates. Think of carbs as little sponges. When you eat carbohydrates, your body converts them into glycogen for energy storage. The catch? **For every gram of glycogen you store, your body hangs onto about 3 to 4 grams of water.**

When you are eating a standard high-carb diet, you are essentially walking around carrying a heavy water backpack.

**Enter the Carnivore Diet:**
When you cut the carbs and switch to meat, your body depletes those glycogen stores. And when the glycogen goes? The water goes with it. This is often called the "Whoosh" effect. It’s why many carnivores lose several pounds in the first week alone—it’s mostly water weight, and a lot of it comes right off your face!

## It’s Not Just Water, It’s Inflammation

Water retention is one piece of the puzzle, but inflammation is the other. Many plant-based foods contain anti-nutrients or potential irritants (like lectins and gluten) that can cause low-level systemic inflammation in sensitive individuals.

Inflammation is essentially the body's swelling response to injury or irritation. When you remove inflammatory triggers and focus on nutrient-dense animal proteins and fats, your body can finally calm down.

**The result?** The redness fades, the swelling subsides, and your skin often clears up.

## Hello, Cheekbones!

So, what does this de-bloating combo look like in the mirror?

* **Sharper Jawline:** That definition you thought was gone forever? It was just hiding behind a layer of water.
* **Bigger Eyes:** Less puffiness around the eyes makes you look more awake and alert.
* **Defined Features:** Your natural bone structure starts to pop.

It’s often referred to as the "Carnivore Glow Up," and for good reason. You aren't just losing weight; you are losing the *volume* that was distorting your natural features.

## A Quick Pro-Tip: Don't Forget the Salt!

Because you are flushing out so much water, you are flushing out electrolytes (sodium, potassium, magnesium) along with it. While we want to lose the bloat, we don't want to get dehydrated!

Make sure you are salting your meat liberally. It sounds counterintuitive—we are usually told salt causes bloating—but on a low-carb diet, your kidneys excrete sodium much faster. You need that salt to keep your energy stable and avoid the "keto flu."

## The Bottom Line

If you are tired of feeling puffy, sluggish, and swollen, give the steak and eggs a try for 30 days. You might be surprised to find that under that "Moon Face" was a superhero jawline waiting to be revealed!


